313
0:17:32,6 --> 0:17:34,133
(applause)


314
0:17:34,133 --> 0:17:40,467
You're not too strapped.


315
0:17:40,467 --> 0:17:43,1
So Congress can
do that right now.


316
0:17:43,1 --> 0:17:44,633
Everybody says
they agree with it.


317
0:17:44,633 --> 0:17:45,7
Let's get it done.


318
0:17:45,7 --> 0:17:48,767
(applause)


319
0:17:48,767 --> 0:17:52,233
So that's the bare minimum.


320
0:17:52,233 --> 0:17:54,633
That's the bare minimum we
should be doing in order to


321
0:17:54,633 --> 0:17:55,633
the grow the economy.


322
0:17:55,633 --> 0:17:57,166
But we can do more.


323
0:17:57,166 --> 0:18:0,867
We can do more than just
extend middle-class tax cuts.


324
0:18:0,867 --> 0:18:6,934
I've said I will work with
Republicans on a plan for


325
0:18:6,934 --> 0:18:11,567
economic growth, job creation,
and reducing our deficits.


326
0:18:11,567 --> 0:18:13,4
And that has some
compromise between


327
0:18:13,4 --> 0:18:14,6
Democrats and Republicans.


328
0:18:14,6 --> 0:18:18,433
I understand people have
a lot of different views.


329
0:18:18,433 --> 0:18:21,266
I'm willing to
compromise a little bit.


330
0:18:21,266 --> 0:18:23,767
But if we're serious about
reducing our deficit,


331
0:18:23,767 --> 0:18:25,834
we've also got to be serious
about investing in the things


332
0:18:25,834 --> 0:18:28,3
that help us grow and make
the middle class strong,


333
0:18:28,3 --> 0:18:31,533
like education, and
research and development,


334
0:18:31,533 --> 0:18:34,667
and making sure kids can go
to college, and rebuilding our


335
0:18:34,667 --> 0:18:36,767
roads and our infrastructure.


336
0:18:36,767 --> 0:18:37,467
(applause)


337
0:18:37,467 --> 0:18:39,433
We've got to do that.


338
0:18:39,433 --> 0:18:44,133
So when you put it all together,
what you need is a package that


339
0:18:44,133 --> 0:18:48,9
keeps taxes where they are for
middle-class families; we make


340
0:18:48,9 --> 0:18:52,166
some tough spending cuts on
things that we don't need;


341
0:18:52,166 --> 0:18:54,567
and then we ask the wealthiest
Americans to pay a slightly


342
0:18:54,567 --> 0:18:56,734
higher tax rate.


343
0:18:56,734 --> 0:19:0,1
And that's a principle I won't
compromise on, because I'm not


344
0:19:0,1 --> 0:19:4,934
going to have a situation
where the wealthiest among us,


345
0:19:4,934 --> 0:19:8,66
including folks like me, get
to keep all our tax breaks,


346
0:19:8,66 --> 0:19:13,5
and then we're asking students
